This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and deep learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with resource-efficient image classification, which could also place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The use of deep neural networks and architectural blocks also suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the mention of mobile convolutional neural networks could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
